  "prompt": "What are some of the best YouTube videos everyone should watch?",
  "response": "Choosing the best YouTube videos can be quite subjective as it depends on individual interests, preferences, and what one considers \"best.\" However, there are some universally acclaimed videos across different genres that have resonated with a wide audience. Here are some suggestions across various categories:\n\n**Inspirational/TED Talks:**\n1. **TED Talks - How great leaders inspire action | Simon Sinek**: A fantastic talk on leadership and inspiration.\n2. **TED Talks - The power of vulnerability | Bren\u00e9 Brown**: An inspiring talk on embracing vulnerability.\n\n**Educational:**\n1. **Vsauce**: Start with \"The Banach-Tarski Paradox\" to dive into mind-bending concepts.\n2. **Kurzgesagt \u2013 In a Nutshell**: Try \"The Egg\" for a profound reflection on existence.\n\n**Documentary/Informational:**\n1. **The Story of Stuff**: A thought-provoking documentary on consumer culture.\n2. **The Most Dangerous Stretch of Water in the World**: A fascinating look at the Mediterranean migration crisis.\n\n**Historical:**\n1. **Oversimplified**: The channel provides fun and engaging animated history lessons.\n2. **CrashCourse**: \"World History: The Renaissance\" gives a great overview of this important era.\n\n**Science/Tech:**\n1. **Smarter Every Day**: Check out \"How AR-15s Work\" to explore complex mechanisms in firearms.\n2. **Mark Rober**: His \"Glitter Bomb Trap\" videos explore amazing practical engineering solutions for a common problem.\n\n**Entertainment/Culture:**\n1. **Bon App\u00e9tit (Channel)**: Particularly the series \u201cGourmet Makes\u201d where professionals attempt to recreate popular snacks.\n2. **Hot Ones \u2013 First We Feast**: Interviews with celebrities while they eat increasingly spicy wings.\n\n**Heartwarming/Feel-Good:**\n1. **Markiplier \u2013 A Heist with Markiplier**: An interactive and fun adventure video.\n2. **Humans of New York**: Powerful personal stories told by everyday people.\n\n**Music/Performances:** \n1. **OK Go \u2013 The One Moment**: Known for their innovative and visually striking music videos.\n2. **Tiny Desk Concerts (NPR)**: Live performances by popular and up-and-coming musicians.\n\n**Comedy:**\n1. **Key & Peele**: Many sketches from the show are available on Comedy Central's YouTube page \u2013 \"Substitute Teacher\" is a standout.\n2. **Last Week Tonight with John Oliver**: Insightful and hilarious takes on current events.\n\n**Art and Creativity:**\n1. **The Slow Mo Guys**: Astonishing slow-motion videos that capture everyday wonders.\n2. **Binging with Babish**: Combining creativity with food, watch how he recreates iconic dishes from movies and TV shows.\n\nRemember, this list can be just a starting point! YouTube is full of incredible content across diverse genres, and there's something for every taste and interest.",
